51.9	Filesystem_in_Userspace	Filesystem in Userspace	Filesystem in Userspace is a loadable kernel module for Unix-like computer operating systems that lets non-privileged users create their own file systems without editing kernel code. This is achieved by running file system code in user space while the FUSE module provides only a "bridge" to the actual kernel interfaces.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/08/FUSE_structure.svg/280px-FUSE_structure.svg.png
